<paragraph blockId="5.[151,684,904,1084]" pageId="5" pageNumber="60">
This species approaches 
<taxonomicName box="[449,612,904,931]" class="Liliopsida" family="Orchidaceae" genus="Disperis" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" pageId="5" pageNumber="60" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="oppositifolia">
<emphasis box="[449,612,904,931]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="60">D. oppositifolia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
but it is distinguished by its flower which is smaller and has lateral sepals that are not strongly united at the base, and a trilobed appendage to the lip that has pubescent lateral lobes shorter than the glabrous midlobe.
</paragraph>
